			<description><![CDATA[<p>
We believe small businesses can change their communities and the world for the better. Our goal is to help them succeed. We focus on helping them communicate with the people that matter.</p>
<p>
CakeMail is looking for a Marketing Analytics and Performance Manager to be based out of our Montreal office.</p>
<p>
In this role, you&rsquo;ll be responsible to implement direct customer acquisition strategies, track the customer journey and optimize for conversion and customer experience.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage, analyze and report on direct customer acquisition channels.</li>
<li>
Test and optimize landing pages.</li>
<li>
Measure customer experience with analytics and surveys.</li>
<li>
Ensure proper tagging of properties for a complete view of the customer journey.</li>
<li>
Define and measure KPIs that align with our company goals.</li>
<li>
Create dashboards and reports for marketing team and management.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Must haves</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Expert in Google Analytics, including multi-channel customer journey reports.</li>
<li>
Expert in Microsoft Excel.</li>
<li>
Working knowledge of HTML and CSS.</li>
<li>
Experience with SEO, SEM and display ads.</li>
<li>
Familiar with advanced marketing metrics, particularly in the B2B space.</li>
<li>
2-4 years experience in a marketing analytics role.</li>
<li>
Have excellent written and verbal communication skills (English).</li>
<li>
Meticulous and detail oriented.</li>
<li>
Have a good sense of humor.<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus points</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience with Mixpanel.</li>
<li>
Background in economics and statistics.</li>
<li>
Experience with a marketing automation suite.</li>
<li>
Multilingual (French, Spanish, Portuguese, etc.).</li>
<li>
Ability to write SQL queries.</li>
<li>
Experience with email marketing.</li>
<li>
Like cupcakes.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Applicants who use creative ways to get our attention do get attention.</p>
<p>
We will not respond to unsolicited recruiters.</p>
<p>
Keywords: analytics, performance, automation, optimization, growth, customer acquisition, customer experience, marketing operations, conversions</p>
